cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with knowledge harvesting, extraction, and mining tasks, which are typically associated with information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also analyzes the lag between news and Wikipedia, which involves temporal modeling and analysis, a topic that falls under the scope of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of resources like DBpedia and YAGO, which are knowledge bases that are typically associated with data mining and machine learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper deals with emergent entities and events, which are related to the study of complex systems (cs.CY).
